(- Executive Summary) Tj
T*
(Atho is a UTXO blockchain built for deterministic validation, operational clarity, and) Tj
T*
(post-quantum readiness. It combines Falcon-512 signatures, SHA3-based hashing, Base56 user) Tj
T*
(addresses, and LMDB-backed state storage.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The objective is to keep consensus behavior explainable, node roles explicit, and state drift) Tj
T*
(low across node, wallet, GUI, and explorer surfaces.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Project phase at this snapshot: **Alpha hardening**.) Tj
T*
(- Origin and History) Tj
T*
(Atho started as an operator-first chain project. Early development exposed role confusion, stale) Tj
T*
(UI/API state, weak incident traceability, and fragile restart behavior.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Development then shifted toward hardening:) Tj
T*
(- stronger validation and payout checks,) Tj
T*
(- cleaner role boundaries,) Tj
T*
(- more explicit node lifecycle control,) Tj
T*
(- and better structured logs for audit and recovery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This paper preserves mission and context while removing stale implementation detail.) Tj
T*
(- Vision and Principles) Tj
T*
(Atho follows five principles:) Tj
T*
(- Determinism: identical data should produce identical validation outcomes.) Tj
T*
(- Auditability: operators must be able to explain failures quickly.) Tj
T*
(- Role clarity: full/miner/wallet behavior must remain explicit.) Tj
T*
(- Cryptographic modernization: post-quantum and SHA3-first direction.) Tj
T*
(- Operational resilience: failures should be visible and recoverable.) Tj
T*
(- Problems Atho Solves) Tj
T*
(Atho targets practical infrastructure issues:) Tj
T*
(- state drift across chain, mempool, wallet, and explorer,) Tj
T*
(- miner payout mismatches from stale defaults,) Tj
T*
(- limited visibility into emission, fee, and coinbase anomalies,) Tj
T*
(- and long-term risk from legacy cryptographic assumptions.) Tj
T*
(- Architecture and Network Design) Tj
T*
(5.1 Identity and Addressing) Tj
T*
